column1: I am a woman who is passionate about life, education and travel. I will educate myself at any given opportunity whether through self study, formal classes or through travel. I am looking for a partner who shares the same passions as I and more... as I want to travel, discover and explore the world with him, making memorable moments no matter where in the world we are, as long as we are together. I am a very cultural woman who thrives on learning about and experiencing other cultures. Honesty, love and respect are crucial to me in any relationship as I feel they all three go hand in hand. If one of those elements is missing, then there is no relationship in my eyes. I one day hope to be happily married, sharing life together with my partner and of course learning from him as well. My immediate family consists of my father and 1 brother. My father is retired from the local utility company and my mother, who has recently passed away, was retired from their local school system. I also have 1 maternal grandmother living and whom I adore. My family is supportive of me and allows me to make my own decisions but yet gently guides me when guidance may be needed. I do live on my own with my children (50/50 basis), all whom are teens. I'm not looking for a "father" for my children, they have their own father who is actively a part of their lives, but I would expect that you be a friend to the children, guiding them and mentoring them. column1: I am a firm believer of God's GRACE in every aspect of our life whether small or big. column1: I am a cheerful Sagittarian looking for a partner to share the ups and downs of life, where we can be each others best friend. Born in Kolkata but educated across India, I have had a cosmopolitan upbringing. After graduation / post graduation in International Relations from Jadavpur University, Kolkata and a few years working in Kolkata, I moved to Mumbai where I am currently working in a managerial role and enjoying it to the hilt. At the same time I have reached a stage where I would like to share my life with that one special person. My likes - I like to travel (have travelled in India & abroad), books (across genres, currently interested in self development), music (once trained in Indian classical, hope to get back to it), eating out (I enjoy restaurants & home cooked food altho not much of a cook yet), and perhaps, most importantly, the company of family and friends. I was not born to be a loner :-) It is always hard to define who we are looking for without sounding inflexible but I would ideally like my partner to be affectionate, fun loving, with a good sense of humour. I am looking for an individual with diverse interests. He could be living anywhere, doing anything. I believe that relationships have to take time to grow, that it develops in a continuum rather than just pop up at a point in time. I would therefore like to start off as friends and see where that takes us. I look forward to getting to know you.,,,,03 Dec 1969,,India,,,,,Kayastha,,,,,,Self,MA (Arts),"43 yrs, 5ft 1in,

I would describe myself as a kind, generous, easy-going person. I love to laugh and enjoy funny situations. I enjoy traveling and the adventures of the outdoors. Getting away is important because I think everyone should see what else is out there. I also like going to the movies, theatre, concerts, museums or a nice restaurant. But I am just as happy staying home and hanging out friends and family. I would like to meet someone who has similar interests, but who can introduce different activities into my life. My ideal match would be someone who is kind and considerate, generous and thoughtful, easy-going and funny. Someone who is not chained to their job, their computer or cell phone would be a plus. Nothing wrong with being a go-getter, but there has to be a good balance, don't you think? Someone who is mature, responsible and intelligent. Someone who puts butterflies in my stomach. Someone who effortlessly makes me laugh. Someone who isn't afraid to make a decision if needed. It would be nice to find a relationship where each person's personality and attitude compliments the other. I also think building upon a friendship first is the way to go.,,,,01 Jan 1970,,United States of America,,,,,Others,,,,,,Self,10th,"43 yrs, 5ft 6in,
